Place the lotus root in a bowl, cover with hot water, and let stand at least 30 minutes to reconsititute. Cut into small pieces and set aside. Place the kombu, burdock, and ginger in the bottom of a large heavy pot or Dutch oven. Top with the lotus root, rutabaga, daikon, celery root, onions, carrots, and parsnips. Add the water to the pot, cover, and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 50 minutes or until the vegetables are tender. Add the shoyu and simmer 5 minutes more. Place the kuzu in a small bowl. Add the cold water and stir to dissolve. Add to the stew and cook, stirring often, until the sauce thickens. Ladle the hot stew into bowls, garnish with scallions, and serve. Variations: â€¢ White turnips, sweet potatoes, taro potatoes, and or winter squash can be substituted for any of the vegetables in this recipe.